Look back in the archived messages and you&#39;ll see ... it turned into sort 
of fun and games though.

The tags on the mattress are supposed to indicate whether the mattress has 
been used or not.  If the tag has been removed, then the mattress has been 
used. A store has to either sell the mattress with the tag intact, 
indicating it is new, or throw it away with the tag missing, which means 
it has been used.

When you buy it, you&#39;re supposed to remove the tag.

I guess this law was passed to try to prevent people from getting cooties 
or diseases or something from the previous owner ...

Zack

